{"blocks":[{"key":"52g24","text":" For analysis, regions of interest (ROIs) were placed on each bouton, and average intensities were
obtained for each frame within the time-lapse. Fmax was defined as the maximal fluorescence after NH4Cl perfusion. Baseline F0 was defined as the average fluorescence of the initial 10 frames before stimulation [(F0 = average (F1:F10)]. Fluorescence intensity of a bouton at a given time point (F) was normalized to F0 and Fmax and expressed as (F-F0) / (Fmax-F0).


